Make every day epic

A dream becomes reality

The performance you want and functionality you need. Stingray offers the perfect combination of performance driving, sculpted design and cargo capacity.

Design

Stingray offers the ultimate blend of striking design, premium materials, and surprising versatility.

Step into luxury

This cockpit combines advanced technology with expert craftsmanship – all wrapped in genuine leather.
Retractable hardtop

Top down, up for anything

The Stingray convertible features a power-retractable roof that flows seamlessly into the body design.

Wheels and seats

With multiple eye-catching leather seat designs to choose from and a variety of wheel options, there are even more ways to customize your Stingray.

GT1

Standard on 1LT and 2LT, the GT1 seat is wrapped in genuine Mulan leather and is designed for long-distance comfort and support.

GT2

Available on 2LT and standard on 3LT, the GT2 seat features carbon-fiber trim with a seatback halo and is wrapped in genuine Napa leather.

Competition Sport

The available Competition Sport seats are wrapped in Napa leather with performance textile in high-wear areas. On 1LT, the performance textile covers the entire seat.

Sterling Silver-painted forged-aluminum wheels

19-inch front and 20-inch rear 5-split-spoke machined-face Sterling Silver-painted forged-aluminum wheels

Graphite forged-aluminum wheels

19-inch front and 20-inch rear 5-split-spoke Satin Graphite forged-aluminum wheels

Performance

Stingray features a naturally aspirated V8 that’s positioned behind the driver, putting more power to the rear wheels where it matters most. And with a quarter-mile time of just 11.2 seconds*(5) and an available 495 horsepower,*(6) Stingray gives any driver the pulse-pounding ride they crave.

8-speed
dual-clutch transmission

470 lb.-ft. of torque*(7)
Available

Magnetic Selective Ride ControlTM 4.0
Available

  • Lightning-quick shifting

    The standard 8-speed dual-clutch transmission combines the smoothness of an automatic with the control of a manual, giving you quicker times – lap after lap.

    Next-generation damping

    Available Magnetic Selective Ride Control™ 4.0 features an innovative suspension fluid containing metal particles that align to change fluid viscosity, giving you the confidence and control to push harder while staying planted.

Corvette Academy
Driver Modes

The Driver Mode Selector is standard on all models and allows you to choose from preset Weather, Tour, Sport and Track Modes as well as customizable MyMode.

Previous model year wheels shown.
Dual-clutch transmission operation

You can manually upshift or downshift your Corvette with paddle shifters on the steering wheel.

Previous model year wheels shown.
Front lift

With the push of a button, a hydraulic lift raises the front end of Corvette almost two inches in under three seconds at speeds below 24 mph.
Memory settings

The driver and passenger seat, mirror and steering wheel settings can be saved for two drivers. Corvette will then recognize who’s driving by the key fob, giving you a personalized driving experience every time.

Driver assistance features

Your Corvette is equipped with available driver assistance features*(8) that can help you avoid collisions while driving, backing up and parking.
